  "prompt": "Where can I learn Spanish in Delhi?",
  "response": "Delhi offers a variety of options for learning Spanish, catering to different preferences and budgets. Here are some popular places where you can learn Spanish in Delhi:\n\n1. **Instituto Cervantes**: Located in Connaught Place, Instituto Cervantes is a globally recognized Spanish cultural institute. It offers comprehensive Spanish language courses from beginner to advanced levels.\n\n2. **Jawaharlal Nehru University (JNU)**: JNU\u2019s School of Language, Literature and Culture Studies offers degree courses and elective Spanish language programs.\n\n3. **Delhi University (DU)**: Several colleges under DU, such as St. Stephen's College and Lady Shri Ram College, offer Spanish language courses.\n\n4. **Jamia Millia Islamia University**: The university offers short-term and long-term Spanish language courses through its Centre for European and Latin American Studies.\n\n5. **Academia De Espa\u00f1ol**: Located in Hauz Khas, Academia De Espa\u00f1ol provides customized Spanish language programs for beginners, intermediates, and advanced learners.\n\n6. **Institute of Spanish Studies**: This institute offers structured Spanish language courses and cultural immersion programs.\n\n7. **Multibhashi**: An online platform offering Spanish lessons via live classes and self-paced resources.\n\n8. **LanguageNext**: Located in Noida (near Delhi), LanguageNext offers Spanish language classes conducted by experienced instructors.\n\n9. **World Languages Centre**: Located in Connaught Place, this institute offers Spanish language courses, focusing on conversation, grammar, and cultural aspects.\n\nAdditionally, there are numerous private tutors and local language institutes throughout Delhi that you can explore for personalized learning experiences. Many online platforms such as Duolingo, Babbel, or Coursera also provide Spanish courses that could complement your in-person lessons.",
